g.text: AoiRank5Convo1 begins.

g.title: j2927008713
g.text: I've never thanked u for being so cool with Eleanor

g.title: j247093
g.text: so thank u <RETRO_EMOJI_HEART>

g.title: j2960310816
g.text: You don’t need to thank me, but I appreciate it.

g.title: j3275659225
g.text: Of course. She’s part of the Hex.

g.title: j1818005762
g.text: You were worried I would be mean to her?

g.title: j3092780439
g.text: u wouldn’t have been the first in the Hex to be wary of Eleanor. and, trust me, I love everyone in the Hex, so I would've understood—but I also would’ve worked hard to change ur mind.

g.title: j2055118981
g.text: People doubted Eleanor? Seriously?

g.title: j850222477
g.text: I find it hard to believe Arthur ever tolerated people being wary of his sister.

g.title: j224970347
g.text: in the early days, Lettie and Quincy had their doubts. they worried she might go full-tech-rot. Arthur wouldn’t hear it, so they kept their concerns quiet, but we all felt it on some level. and if *we* sensed it, imagine how sharp and clear it was to Eleanor

g.title: j770959592
g.text: Thank Sol for Arthur. He’s a good brother.

g.title: j28347213
g.text: That must have been unbearable for her, always knowing what people were thinking.

g.title: j2511401119
g.text: I’m really disappointed in Lettie and Quincy.

g.title: j4133992630
g.text: he is, ya. but I think that made things even harder for Eleanor back then. he was desperate to protect her, and she knew that if he ever believed she was suffering too much because of the infestation, he might take matters into his own hands

g.title: j4131918394
g.text: they were just scared. fear makes people act in strange ways.

g.title: j3504827900
g.text: You’re saying he might’ve... killed his own sister?

g.title: j1587103805
g.text: The fear of losing control must have been terrifying. Especially with Arthur watching over her like that.

g.title: j890126336
g.text: Clearly, the team has come a long way since then.

g.title: j2426026138
g.text: I wish they could have seen past their fear back then.

g.title: j1747417858
g.text: I never thought he would kill her, but Eleanor did. why she thought that is between her and Arthur. I’m just glad she doesn’t feel that way anymore.

g.title: j2375900260
g.text: I’ve heard it said that what really traumatizes people isn’t what happens to them, but how they react to it. knowing who Lettie and Quincy are at heart, I’m sure if their fear had led to anything happening to Eleanor, they’d never have forgiven themselves.

g.title: j2276502092
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j520071004
g.text: It’s hard to imagine her carrying that kind of fear on top of everything else.

g.title: j2178027209
g.text: Did she ever come close to leaving because of it?

g.title: j518204690
g.text: Did it almost come to that?

g.title: j1496017757
g.text: It’s hard to blame them for being human, I guess.

g.title: j1845249184
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j3130499342
g.text: after her transformation, Eleanor paid close attention to how everyone reacted. I could see her weighing her options, thinking she might do more harm than good by staying. she wanted to help the Hex, but the way some people looked at her made her wonder if she could help more from a distance.

g.title: j1262562974
g.text: That’s ridiculous. With psychic powers like hers? She’s invaluable.

g.title: j2280888989
g.text: That’s so unfair. They didn’t see how much she was willing to give up for the Hex.

g.title: j1859569270
g.text: she thought she could use her powers from afar, stay connected without burdening us with her presence.

g.title: j747569581
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j3812388046
g.text: I see. She was willing to sacrifice being with the team just to make them feel safe.

g.title: j2759993041
g.text: Being alone in Höllvania would have put her in so much danger.

g.title: j3646047288
g.text: one night, when even Amir had gone to sleep, she actually did almost leave. quietly, in the dead of night. she didn’t even want to burden us with goodbyes.

g.title: j1471681838
g.text: That’s heartbreaking.

g.title: j1118060961
g.text: Luckily for everyone, she clearly didn't.

g.title: j2761773545
g.text: She must have felt so alone at that moment.

g.title: j1265865931
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j269158893
g.text: I hate to imagine what could have happened... I’d been keeping an eye on her tho, trying to be there for her.

g.title: j1652231881
g.text: u know that feeling when ur with someone but they’re not really there? when their mind keeps drifting, no matter how much they try to stay present? I noticed that...

g.title: j1043861045
g.text: It sounds like you were exactly what she needed in that moment.

g.title: j1472650168
g.text: When it comes to the team's happiness, nothing gets past you.

g.title: j3056066831
g.text: I wasn't sure how much of her distance was just her learning to manage her psychic powers or her consciously checking how people saw her. so, I started keeping tabs on her too.

g.title: j1750069115
g.text: the second I sensed her atomicycle booting up, I locked down every atomicycle in the garage and ran out to stop her.

g.title: j4177347424
g.text: So it was you. You’re the reason she stayed.

g.title: j424917620
g.text: That was brave.

g.title: j3070558303
g.text: I would’ve let her go if that’s what she really wanted. but she wasn’t leaving without a heart-to-heart with me first, haha.

g.title: j424389679
g.text: That’s so you haha. I’m guessing the heart-to-heart went well?

g.title: j550169299
g.text: I’m glad you were there for her. That night probably changed everything for her.

g.title: j3270699511
g.text: And that heart-to-heart probably saved her—and the Hex.

g.title: j1348181667
g.text: oh, we talked until the sun came up. since Amir was asleep, we even played some pinball—just the two of us.

g.title: j1536581295
g.text: it was silly and fun, the kind of fun Eleanor desperately needed.

g.title: j178619688
g.text: How did you convince her that everything was okay?

g.title: j3355770864
g.text: Sometimes, the simplest things make the biggest difference.

g.title: j110813317
g.text: I don’t think it was any one thing I said. it was just... being there. being a friend.

g.title: j3687130199
g.text: it was the first time since her transformation that someone showed her she was more than Arthur’s fragile sister to be protected. I think that night helped her see she could carve out her own place in the Hex.

g.title: j2292507289
g.text: I’m glad you did that. She needed it.

g.title: j3130279084
g.text: That’s what true leadership looks like, Aoi.

g.title: j2497470453
g.text: I need it too, honestly. we’re all stronger when we know we belong.

g.title: j529550383
g.text: Eleanor’s stronger than people give her credit for, but having you by her side made all the difference.

g.title: j3777621604
g.text: Well, I commend you for keeping the team together.

g.title: j104226315
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j190038011
g.text: I guess I just realized, having u join us, we could have relived that whole awful chapter again

g.title: j3465259627
g.text: but we didn't have to. u understood right away

g.title: j4019644040
g.text: so thank u

g.title: j2846041058
g.text: Eleanor deserves to be seen for the amazing woman she is.

g.title: j1002160454
g.text: It was nothing. We've got to have each other's backs.

g.title: j3034384236
g.text: Thanks for being there for Eleanor.

g.title: j1337772136
g.text: You're the glue that holds this team together, Aoi.

g.title: j3767351029
g.text: ur one of my favorite people <RETRO_EMOJI_HEART> just so u know

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.
